Last week, President Biden suspended a shipment of weapons to Israel to prevent American manufacturing weapons from being used in an assault on Rafah, said yesterday by the White House.&nbsp; "We paused a shipment of weapons last week. This is 1,800 2,000-pounder bombs (907 kg) and 1,700 500-pounder bombs (226 kg)", said a high administration official who wanted to keep the anonymity, adding that "we have not yet made a definitive decision on how to proceed with this expedition".
&nbsp;
Activists and relatives of the hostages have blocked the Ayalon motorway in Tel Aviv> during the morning peak hour. The protesters, who prevent the circulation of traffic in the north direction to the junction of Rokach, call for an agreement with Hamas for the release of the kidnapped. Israel is expected to arrive at the head of the CIA, William Burns, for talks with Prime Minister Netanyahu.
&nbsp;
<h2>Idf, we have planned that war will last a year
"We planned a war lasting about a year. Gaza is perhaps one of the most difficult arenas in the world." The Idf spokesman, Daniel Hagari, said this at the conference organized by Yediot Ahronoth.
"We did not enter Rafah three or four months ago because&nbsp; there were no operating conditions to do so," he added. "Even after we face Rafah there will be terrorism. Hamas will move north and try to reorganize. Wherever Hamas returns, we will act," Hagari assured.
